In 2020 , gross enrolment ratio in secondary education for Rwanda was 72.1 % . Gross enrolment ratio in secondary education of Rwanda increased from 43.1 % in 2006 to 72.1 % in 2020 growing at an average annual rate of 3.66 % .

The statistic shows the business service output index for the Republic of Ireland from 2010 to June 2021 . The business service output index is a composite indicator based on the production output of business services . The business services sector comprises activities of administrative and support services , except education ; accounting , auditing and bookkeeping ; legal services ; management consultancy and technical testing and analysis . In 2021 , the business services output index was at a level of 111.9 index points , up from 105.5 index points in 2010 .

In 2019 , out-of-school children for Nepal was 1.1 million . Between 1990 and 2019 , out-of-school children in Nepal grew substantially from 408,305 to 1.1 million rising at an increasing annual rate that reached a peak of 19.97 % in 2005 and then decreased to 18.89 % in 2019 .

In 2018 , private enrolment in secondary education for Republic of Korea was 66.9 % . Though Republic of Korea private enrolment in secondary education fluctuated substantially in recent years , it tended to decrease through 1999 - 2018 period ending at 66.9 % in 2018 .
Between 1992 and 2018 , Republic of Moldova renewable water resources remained stable at around 11 billion cubic meters per year .

In 2018 , maternal mortality ( death ) for Malaysia was 2.18 deaths per 100,000 live births . Though Malaysia maternal mortality ( death ) fluctuated substantially in recent years , it tended to increase through 2003 - 2018 period ending at 2.18 deaths per 100,000 live births in 2018 .
